body:
I would like to override the default json-schema used by VSCode on some files with my own json-schema (example: VSCode use a json-schema for the Node's "package.json", but I want to be able to override it), like when configuring any other json-schema in settings.json:
```
//settings.json - currently this doesn't work and VSCode keep applying the Node's package.json json-schema
"json.schemas": [{
	"fileMatch": ["*/package.json"],
	"url": "./schemas/package.json"
}]
```

Reason is: I'm working on a project where there's a file called "package.json" which is not related to Node: it's something completely different and internal to the project, and it's not even in the root directory, but I can't rename it and VSCode wrongly use the Node's json-schema and everything become an error.

**Problem**
`Action` is a subclass of disposable because a few of its subclasses register listeners or other handlers that should be disposed of. However while investigating leakage of disposables, I noticed that we are not calling dispose on many actions that are created.

I'm not sure if this is causing any issues currently as only a subset of `Action` subclasses actually need to be disposable. 

**Repo**
1. Enable the `TRACK_DISPOSABLES` flag here: 
https://github.com/microsoft/vscode/blob/2641bd536d53d34962b7a09496c1f421d9dfd0e3/src/vs/base/common/lifecycle.ts#L15
 
    Note that this results in a lot of logging of false positives

1.  Open OSS build and open a single editor
1. Open dev tools and wait a moment for the `__is_disposable_tracked__` messages to stop being printing. Then clear the dev tools console
1. Now split the editor and then close the split editor quickly to return to the original state

**Bug**
Note the warnings in the devtools console about various subclasses of `Action` not being disposed of properly. The printed call stack will start with:

```
at trackDisposable (lifecycle.ts:38)
    at new Disposable (lifecycle.ts:132)
    at new Action (actions.ts:68)
    ...
```

<img width="690" alt="Screen Shot 2019-06-05 at 4 18 54 PM" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/12821956/58996574-a216b580-87ad-11e9-9879-bd34e08bb21b.png">

I've also confirmed this issue by adding some tracking in `Action` itself:

```diff
diff --git a/src/vs/base/common/actions.ts b/src/vs/base/common/actions.ts
index 778a4e9f14..a8278b6215 100644
--- a/src/vs/base/common/actions.ts
+++ b/src/vs/base/common/actions.ts
@@ -48,6 +48,8 @@ export interface IActionChangeEvent {
 	radio?: boolean;
 }
 
+let actionCount = 0;
+
 export class Action extends Disposable implements IAction {
 
 	protected _onDidChange = this._register(new Emitter<IActionChangeEvent>());
@@ -64,6 +66,7 @@ export class Action extends Disposable implements IAction {
 
 	constructor(id: string, label: string = '', cssClass: string = '', enabled: boolean = true, actionCallback?: (event?: any) => Promise<any>) {
 		super();
+		++actionCount ;
 		this._id = id;
 		this._label = label;
 		this._cssClass = cssClass;
@@ -71,6 +74,12 @@ export class Action extends Disposable implements IAction {
 		this._actionCallback = actionCallback;
 	}
 
+	dispose() {
+		--actionCount;
+		console.log(`Actions = ${actionCount }`);
+		super.dispose();
+	}
+
 	get id(): string {
 		return this._id;
 	}
```
